description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a qualified Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (Health Visitor)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Currently we have four vacancies, three in the Alfreton Health Visiting team and one in the Heanor Health Visiting team, all within the Amber Valley locality.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All posts are part time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Health Visitor, do you have a passion in supporting children and families and would like to work in Derbyshire Community Health Service Foundation Trust which has gained recognition for being outstanding by CQC?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like a new challenge in a new area?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, read on ……&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint innovative and motivated Health Visitors to join our 0-5 workforce within the wider, 0-19 Children’s service teams in Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will be based within Amber Valley, and are in the Alfreton and Heanor Health Visiting Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carla Dormon, Locality Manager, carladormon@nhs.net, 07776 485989&lt;/p&gt;
